<font color="#FF0000">THANKS TO VETERANS</font><br>
<tt>Fri Feb 21 15:48:01 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
I have a bumper sticker on my car that states, <br>
&quot;If you (HEART) your FREEDOM, Thank a Veteran&quot;. It was given<br>
to me at a &quot;POW/MIA Recognician Day&quot; at Ft. Devons Mass.in<br>
October 1988. It is still on my bumper although it is now<br>
badly weathered. A few months ago while going home from work<br>
a car in the next lane kept tailgateing the car in front of <br>
him. After a few minutes, I slowed to allow the lead car <br>
move over before someone got hurt. The offending car pulled<br>
even with me and waved to get my attention. Once he had it,<br>
he held up a spirel notebook on which he had written,<br>
&quot;THANK YOU for MY FREEDOM&quot;<br>
At first I didn't realize what it meant, but soon it dawned<br>
on me.<br>
Eight years and I get an unexpected &quot;Thank You&quot;! Unexpected<br>
because the driver was young, clean-cut, well-dressed <br>
businessman and I, a longer haired, bearded, working class<br>
type. &quot;Thank you for my Freedom&quot;- that made it almost worth<br>
my cost.<br>
&quot;THANK YOU FOR MY FREEDOM&quot; to ALL VETERANS!!<br>
And Thank for this and all the sites. 
<p><code>-- b2x4x93  (William T. (REB) Marthers) </code><p>


